# URL contract for the web client (copy to .env only if you need overrides).
#
# VITE_API_URL / VITE_WS_URL are explicit overrides for split-origin deploys.
# They only take effect when set to a non-empty string (src/lib/runtimeEnv.ts).
# Leave them unset for the two normal topologies:
#
#   dev:   `npm run dev` proxies API/WS same-origin to the Go server
#          (vite.config.js; backend target defaults to :8088, override with
#          CAMBIA_API_TARGET). The dev server force-derives origin regardless
#          of these keys.
#   prod:  builds derive both URLs from window.location.origin at runtime,
#          so a stale value here can never poison a production build.
#
# Split-origin example (client served from a different origin than the API):
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
# VITE_WS_URL=wss://api.example.com
